gui_deselect(25.10)                                        gui_deselect(25.10)

Name
       gui_deselect - Deselects objects as per the parameters you specify

Syntax
       gui_deselect

       [-help]

       {-all  |

       -rect {<x1 y1 x2 y2>} |

       -point {<x y>} |

       -line {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}}

       Deselects  objects as per the parameters you specify. If -all is speci-
       fied, deselects all selected objects.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each gui_deselect parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man gui_deselect

       -all   Deselects all objects.

       -line {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Deselects objects through which the specified line passes.

       -point {<x y>}
              Deselects objects at the specified point.

       -rect {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Deselects objects within the specified box coordinates.

